    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Isaiah",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 15,
        "summary": "Moab will be laid waste, and her people will howl and weep.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The burden of Moab. Because in the night Ar of Moab is laid waste, and brought to silence; because in the night Kir of Moab is laid waste, and brought to silence;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0a message of doom \u201clifted up\u201d against Moab.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 19:37 (30\u201337); Ezek. 25:8.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 2:9.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 48:4 (1\u201347).",
                        "start": 119,
                        "end": 123
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 139,
                        "end": 142
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He is gone up to Bajith, and to Dibon, the high places, to weep: Moab shall howl over Nebo, and over Medeba: on all their heads shall be baldness, and every beard cut off.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 3:24; Jer. 48:37.",
                        "start": 137,
                        "end": 145
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0in mourning over the destruction.",
                        "start": 163,
                        "end": 170
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 128,
                        "end": 136
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 147,
                        "end": 150
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "In their streets they shall gird themselves with sackcloth: on the tops of their houses, and in their streets, every one shall howl, weeping abundantly.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Heshbon shall cry, and Elealeh: their voice shall be heard even unto Jahaz: therefore the armed soldiers of Moab shall cry out; his life shall be grievous unto him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 48:34.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "My heart shall cry out for Moab; his fugitives shall flee unto Zoar, an heifer of three years old: for by the mounting up of Luhith with weeping shall they go it up; for in the way of Horonaim they shall raise up a cry of destruction.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 16:11; Jer. 48:36.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0Zoar should still have been young and vigorous.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0the ascent of Luhith.",
                        "start": 106,
                        "end": 109
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 48:3.",
                        "start": 184,
                        "end": 192
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For the waters of Nimrim shall be desolate: for the hay is withered away, the grass faileth, there is no green thing.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore the abundance they have gotten, and that which they have laid up, shall they carry away to the brook of the willows.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0probably the border between Moab and Edom.",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 125
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the cry is gone round about the borders of Moab; the howling thereof unto Eglaim, and the howling thereof unto Beer-elim.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Num. 21:16 (16\u201318).",
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 124
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the waters of Dimon shall be full of blood: for I will bring more upon Dimon, lions upon him that escapeth of Moab, and upon the remnant of the land.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
